article.description: Steven Cook scored 21 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead Princeton over Hawaii 75-62 in the Pearl Harbor Invitational on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Princeton beats Hawaii 75-62 in Pearl Harbor Invitational
article.linkText: Princeton beats Hawaii 75-62 in Pearl Harbor Invitational
article.story: HONOLULU -- Steven Cook scored 21 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead Princeton over Hawaii 75-62 in the Pearl Harbor Invitational on Wednesday night. Cook was 7 of 14 from the field and made five 3-pointers. Spencer Weisz added 17 points on 6-of-7 shooting for Princeton (3-4), which shot 26 of 56 from the floor for 46 percent, and made 13 of 15 free throws. Henry Caruso had 12 points for the Tigers. Gibson Johnson scored a career-high 19 points for Hawaii (4-5), which has lost three of its last four games. Noah Allen made three 3-point shots and also finished with 19 points. Hawaii used a 15-4 spurt to cut into a 20-point halftime deficit and pull to 47-38 with about 15 minutes left, but they didn't get closer. It was the first meeting between the schools.
